structions from the local Agent, this document had to be signed by a terminal representative in Kalundborg, in order to acknowledge that the cargo had been discharged at the \u0022right\u0022 destination. This document can be requested by local authorities next time the vessel calls Libya.  As vessel discharged the cargo in Savona, P\u0026I club were concerned about potential fines next time Stena Sunrise calls Libya. The solution to avoid these potential fines was to get a few documents in hand such as a signed and stamped letter from Equinor stating that they changed their discharge orders, a letter of undertaking and get the discharge certificate signed by the loading Master in Savona (even though it stated Kalundborg). We managed to gather all the required docs, signatures and stamps, Lesson learned uploaded in BMS. Financially, a nice upswing mainly explained by bunker savings compared to estimates. The ballast voyage was generated basis 13.5 kts to create time at Offshore Malta as we initially were looking at bunkering there, which did not happen due to bad weather and we could therefore proceed at most Eco speed to Es Sider. Furthermore, port consumption in the pre-calculation was based on LSMGO however vessel consumed VLSFO and HSFO. Using scrubber (HSFO) in port is against the Stena scrubber policy, Master and NMM have been reminded and a non-conformity report uploaded in BMS. About $20k added to the freight thanks to overage. Swift port turnarounds resulted in nil demurrage. AWRP for calling Es Sider rebilled to charterers."},{"modifiedDate":"2024-04-10T11:42:46.72","modifiedByFull":"Mohlin, Max","remark":"Bunkers \u002B port costs basis PDA updated"}],"offhireList":[{"id":198516,"dateStartUtc":null,"dateEndUtc":null,"days":null,"displayOrder":0,"offhireReason":null,"remark":null,"offhireBunkerList":[{"id":289939,"gradeName":"HSBF","quantity":null,"price":null,"displayOrder":0}]}],"tcNumber":null,"tcOutIdEncrypted":null,"tcReletDetail":null}